The Commission of Inquiry into State Capture continues to hear Gupta-related evidence from Nomachule Gigaba on Friday. The commission will also hear evidence from former Minister Malusi Gigaba. Live stream this Friday:  The proceedings were adjourned last night due to security concerns. Chair Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo didn’t reveal the details of the security concerns before he stopped Mrs Gigaba’s testimony and asked her to come back Friday morning.